title: Report on TTO Creator Marketplace videos

headers.name: Access-Token
headers.description: Access token authorized by a TikTok One Creator Marketplace account. For details, see Authentication .

headers.name: Country-Code
headers.description: A country or region code that is associated with the TikTok One Creator Marketplace campaign ( campaign_id ). To obtain a valid country or region code associated with the TikTok One Creator Marketplace campaign, use /tto/tcm/campaign/ and select one code from the returned country_codes .

parameters.name: tto_tcm_account_id
parameters.description: The ID of the TikTok One Creator Marketplace account. To obtain the IDs of the accounts that you can access via Access-Token , use /tto/oauth2/tcm/ .

parameters.name: campaign_id
parameters.description: The ID of a TikTok One Creator Marketplace campaign with a campaign-level invite link or brand-level invite link . To create a campaign and obtain the campaign ID, use /tto/tcm/campaign/create/ .

parameters.name: start_date Conditional
parameters.description: Required when end_date is passed. If you specify both start_date and end_date , the response will include the daily_stats parameter that shows the daily metrics for the specified time range. If you don't specify both start_date and end_date , the response will not include the daily metrics ( daily_stats ). Report start date, in the format of YYYY-MM-DD (UTC+0 time). The start_date should not be earlier than the campaign creation time. To obtain the campaign creation time, check the create_time returned from /tto/tcm/campaign/create/ or /tto/tcm/campaign/ . Example: 2024-01-01 .

parameters.name: end_date Conditional
parameters.description: Required when start_date is passed. If you specify both start_date and end_date , the response will include the daily_stats parameter that shows the daily metrics for the specified time range. If you don't specify both start_date and end_date , the response will not include the daily metrics ( daily_stats ). Report end date, in the format of YYYY-MM-DD (UTC+0 time). Example: 2024-02-01 .

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: Current page number. This field specifies which page of results to retrieve. The number of pages is based on the total number of records and the page_size . Default value: 1. Value range: â‰¥ 1.

parameters.name: page_size
parameters.description: Page size. This specifies the number of records (the performance metrics for videos linked to the specified campaign ID) that you try to retrieve for each request. Default value: 25. Value range: 1-100.

top_fields.name: code
top_fields.description: Response code. For the complete list of response codes and descriptions, see Appendix-Return Code .

top_fields.name: message
top_fields.description: Response message. For details, see Appendix - Return Codes .

top_fields.name: request_id
top_fields.description: The log ID of a request, which uniquely identifies the request.

fields.name: tto_tcm_account_id
fields.description: The ID of the TikTok One Creator Marketplace account.

fields.name: campaign_id
fields.description: The ID of the TikTok One Creator Marketplace campaign.

fields.name: country_code
fields.description: A country or region code that is associated with the TikTok One Creator Marketplace campaign.

fields.name: campaign_type
fields.description: The type of the TTO Creator Marketplace campaign. Enum values: CAMPAIGN : A campaign with a campaign-level invite link . BRAND_LINK : A campaign with a brand-level invite link .

fields.name: campaign_channel_type
fields.description: The channel type where the campaign was created. Enum values: STANDARD_CAMPAIGN : A Standard Campaign created on the TikTok One platform. LITE_CAMPAIGN : A Lite Campaign created on the TikTok One platform. API_LITE_CAMPAIGN : A Lite Campaign created via the API.

fields.name: page_info
fields.description: Pagination information.

fields.name: page
fields.description: Current page number.

fields.name: page_size
fields.description: Current page size.

fields.name: total_page
fields.description: Total number of pages.

fields.name: total_number
fields.description: Total number of videos. Note : This number is country-specific and depends on the header parameter Country-Code . For example, if a campaign includes two videos in the US and one video in Canada, total_number will be 2 when Country-Code is set to US , and 1 when set to CA .

fields.name: videos
fields.description: The list of videos that have been linked to the TikTok One Creator Marketplace campaign.

fields.name: video_info
fields.description: Information about the video.

fields.name: create_time
fields.description: The time when the video was published, in the format of YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS (UTC+0 time). Example: 2024-01-01 00:00:01 .

fields.name: embed_url
fields.description: An embeddable link to the TikTok video. This URL can be used to embed the TikTok video in external websites or applications. Example: https://v77.tiktokcdn.com/{{embed_url}} .

fields.name: thumbnail_url
fields.description: Temporary URL for thumbnail of the video. Expiration date-time is included in the x-expires query param as Epoch/Unix time in seconds. Example: https://p16-sign-va.tiktokcdn.com/obj/tos-maliva-p-0068/12345678a12e3456a02017dcf822217e_1725607566?lk3s=c6b69ba0&nonce=51584&refresh_token=73f581ee21c7de32951926a0104f51a2&x-expires=1729173600&x-signature=vIBf8%2Bmp4%2FxXQpKrca1B5%2B%2FfpTU%3D&shp=c6b69ba0&shcp=- .

fields.name: video_id
fields.description: The unique identifier for the video.

fields.name: authorization_code
fields.description: The Spark Ads authorization code for the video.

fields.name: creator_info
fields.description: Information about the TikTok Creator.

fields.name: display_name
fields.description: The display name of the Creator.

fields.name: handle_name
fields.description: The handle name of the Creator.

fields.name: ad_clicks
fields.description: The number of clicks on your ads.

fields.name: ad_conversions
fields.description: The number of times your ad achieved an outcome based on the objective and settings you selected. Note : This field is based on the selected campaign objective and settings.

fields.name: ad_cost
fields.description: Ads cost. The estimated total amount of money you've spent on your campaign, ad group, or ad during its schedule. Updated in real time.

fields.name: ad_cpa
fields.description: Cost per conversion. The average amount of money you've spent on a paid conversion. Updated in real time.

fields.name: ad_cpc
fields.description: The average amount of money you've spent on a paid click.

fields.name: ad_cpm
fields.description: The average amount of money you've spent per 1,000 paid impressions.

fields.name: ad_ctr
fields.description: CTR (destination). The percentage of times people saw your ad and performed a click. Updated in real time.

fields.name: ad_cvr
fields.description: Conversion rate (CVR). The percentage of conversions from all impressions on your ads. Updated in real time.

fields.name: ad_impressions
fields.description: Impressions. The number of times your ads were on screen. Updated in real time.

fields.name: video_views
fields.description: Total views. Total number of times the video has been watched. Updated in real time

fields.name: video_views_organic
fields.description: Organic video views. Total number of views acquired through organic delivery, and not through Spark Ads . Updated in real time

fields.name: video_views_paid
fields.description: Paid views. Total number of views acquired through Spark Ads . Updated in real time

fields.name: reach
fields.description: Reach (Unique viewers). Estimated number of unique users who viewed the video at least once. Updated daily

fields.name: engagement_count
fields.description: Engagement count. Total number of likes ( likes ), shares ( shares ), and comments ( comments ). Updated in real time

fields.name: engagement_rate
fields.description: Engagement rate, calculated as the engagement count ( engagement_count ) divided by the total number of views ( video_views ). Updated in real time

fields.name: engagement_rate_organic
fields.description: Organic engagement rate. The percentage of the audience who interacted with the campaign or video through organic delivery. It is calculated by dividing the number of organic interactions (likes, comments, and shares from non-paid views) by the total number of organic video views. Updated in real time

fields.name: engagement_rate_paid
fields.description: Paid engagement rate. The percentage of the audience who interacted with the campaign or video through Spark Ads. It is calculated by dividing the number of paid interactions (likes, comments, and shares from paid views) by the total number of paid video views. Updated in real time

fields.name: video_completion_rate
fields.description: Video completion rate, calculated as total completed video views divided by the total number of views ( video_views ). Updated in real time for the first seven days after the post was created and then updated daily afterwards

fields.name: likes
fields.description: Likes. Total number of likes associated with the video. Updated in real time

fields.name: likes_organic
fields.description: Organic likes. Total number of likes generated through non-paid (organic) delivery. Updated in real time

fields.name: likes_paid
fields.description: Paid likes. Total number of likes generated through Spark Ads. Updated in real time

fields.name: comments
fields.description: Comments. Total number of comments associated with the video. Updated in real time

fields.name: comments_organic
fields.description: Organic comments. Total number of comments generated through non-paid (organic) delivery. Updated in real time

fields.name: comments_paid
fields.description: Paid comments. Total number of comments generated through Spark Ads. Updated in real time

fields.name: shares
fields.description: Shares. Total number of shares associated with the video. Updated in real time

fields.name: shares_organic
fields.description: Organic shares. Total number of shares generated through non-paid (organic) delivery. Updated in real time

fields.name: shares_paid
fields.description: Paid shares. Total number of shares generated through Spark Ads. Updated in real time

fields.name: total_play_time
fields.description: Total play time, in seconds. Total amount of time users spend watching the video. Updated in real time for the first seven days after the post was created and then updated daily afterwards

fields.name: average_view_time
fields.description: Average view time, in seconds. Average amount of time users spend watching the video, calculated as the total play time ( total_play_time ) divided by views ( video_views ). Updated in real time for the first seven days after the post was created and then updated daily afterwards

fields.name: two_seconds_views
fields.description: 2-Second video views. Percentage of views that lasted more than two seconds, calculated as the number of views that lasted more than 2 seconds divided by views ( video_views ). Updated daily

fields.name: six_seconds_views
fields.description: 6-Second video views. Percentage of views that lasted more than six seconds, calculated as the number of views that lasted more than six seconds divided by views ( video_views ). Updated daily

fields.name: video_view_retention
fields.description: A list of numbers indicating the video retention rate at each second. For instance, the value [1, 0.61, 0.27, 0.2, 0.16, 0.14, 0.11, 0.09, 0.08, 0.07, 0.07, 0.06, 0.05, 0.05, 0.05, 0.04, 0.04] indicates that during the first second, the video retention rate decreases from 100% to 61%. Updated in real time for the first seven days after the post was created and then updated daily afterwards

fields.name: video_views_by_source
fields.description: View sources. Breakdown of how viewers were exposed to the video. Updated in real time for the first seven days after the post was created and then updated daily afterwards

fields.name: for_you
fields.description: Video views from For You page.

fields.name: hashtag
fields.description: Video views from hashtag.

fields.name: sound
fields.description: Video views from sound.

fields.name: personal_profile
fields.description: Video views from personal profile.

fields.name: search
fields.description: Video views from search.

fields.name: following
fields.description: Video views from following.

fields.name: other
fields.description: Video views from other.

fields.name: audience_genders_distribution
fields.description: Breakdown of male and female users among viewers. Updated daily

fields.name: gender
fields.description: Gender. Enum values: FEMALE : female. MALE : male. Note : This field might return null if the system cannot determine the gender.

fields.name: percentage
fields.description: Percentage.

fields.name: audience_countries_distribution
fields.description: Distribution of video views by audience countries. Updated daily

fields.name: country
fields.description: Country or region code. Example: US .

fields.name: percentage
fields.description: Percentage.

fields.name: audience_age_distribution
fields.description: Breakdown of viewers by age group. Updated daily

fields.name: percentage
fields.description: Percentage.

fields.name: audience_device_distribution
fields.description: Breakdown of viewers by operating system. Updated daily

fields.name: device
fields.description: Device operating system. Enum values: android : Android. ios : iOS.

fields.name: percentage
fields.description: Percentage.

fields.name: audience_locale_distribution
fields.description: Breakdown of viewers by state-level locales in the country or region. Only available for the US. Updated daily

fields.name: locale
fields.description: State-level locale. For enum values, see Location IDs .

fields.name: percentage
fields.description: Percentage. Total number of viewers in the state ( locale ) divided by the total number of viewers in the country or region.

fields.name: audience_interest_distribution
fields.description: Breakdown of viewers by interest categories. Updated daily

fields.name: interest_tag
fields.description: The ID of the interest category. To learn about the corresponding interest category name for each interest category ID, see Mapping between interest category ID and name .

fields.name: percentage
fields.description: Percentage.

fields.name: anchor_id
fields.description: The ID of the anchor that is associated with the campaign.

fields.name: anchor_metrics
fields.description: Anchor metrics.

fields.name: anchor_views
fields.description: Anchor views. Total number of times the anchor has been viewed.

fields.name: anchor_clicks
fields.description: Anchor clicks. Total number of clicks on the anchor.

fields.name: anchor_unique_views
fields.description: Unique anchor views. The number of unique viewers who saw the anchor.

fields.name: anchor_unique_clicks
fields.description: Unique anchor clicks. The number of times the anchor was clicked by distinct users.

fields.name: daily_stats
fields.description: Daily statistics breakdown. **Note** : We won't fill in the missing metrics with any default value (such as 0), so if one metric is missing from one day, that means the data is not available.

fields.name: date
fields.description: Date, in the format of YYYY-MM-DD (UTC+0 time).

fields.name: views
fields.description: Total views. Total number of times the video has been watched on the date.

fields.name: video_views_organic
fields.description: Organic video views. Total number of views acquired through organic delivery, and not through Spark Ads on the date.

fields.name: video_views_paid
fields.description: Paid views. Total number of views acquired through Spark Ads on the date.

fields.name: reach
fields.description: Reach (Unique viewers). Estimated number of unique users who viewed the video at least once on the date.

fields.name: engagement_rate
fields.description: Engagement rate, calculated as the total number of likes ( likes ), shares ( shares ), and comments ( comments ) divided by the total number of views ( views ) on the date.

fields.name: video_completion_rate
fields.description: Video completion rate, calculated as total completed video views divided by the total number of views ( views ) on the date.

fields.name: likes
fields.description: Likes. Total number of likes associated with the video on the date.

fields.name: comments
fields.description: Comments. Total number of comments associated with the video on the date.

fields.name: shares
fields.description: Shares. Total number of shares associated with the video on the date.
